HEADWORD: Parturient
<hw>Par*tu"ri*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parturiens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>parturire</ets> to desire to bring
forth, fr. <ets>parere</ets>, <ets>partum</ets>, to bring forth. See
<er>Parent</er>.]</ety> <def>Bringing forth, or about to bring forth,
young; fruitful.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parturifacient</ent>⟦br⟧
